  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Engage farmers in reversing deforestion in Zambia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Zambia&apos;s Copperbelt region, native Miombo woodlands have been disappearing for many decades. WeForest is engaging with and training hundreds of small-scale farmers to restore these forests on their farms. In doing so, the farmers benefit from diversified jobs, higher incomes and new skills! Besides, via the project&apos;s holistic approach that integrates livelihood development with ecological restoration, farmers receive help in obtaining ownership of land.</narrative>
  </description>
